Final Variable

/*
	class test{
		final int x;
		// Here By Default Compiler will Not provide initial value as in case
		of instance variable.
	}
*/
/*
	Final Variable must be initialized before Constructor Completion.
	
	
	So Possibilities:
		1) At the Time Of Declaration
			
			class test{
				final int x=10;
			}
			
		2) Inside Instance block.
			
			class test{
				final int x=10;
				{
					x=10;
				}
			}
		3) Inside Constructor
			
			class test{
				final int x;
				test(){
					x=10;
				}
			}
*/


/*
	class test{
		static int x=10;
		public static void main(String ...args){
			SOP(x);------------------>## Default value will be 0 assigned by the compiler.
		}
	}
*/


/*
	For Final Variable Before Constructor Completion, The final variable must be Initialized
	for Final static Variable, Before Class Loading Completion, the final variable must be initialized.
	
	Possibilities:
		1) At the time of declaration
		2) Inside Static block
*/


/*
	class test{
		public static void main(String ...args){
			final int x;
			sop("Hi");
		}
	}
	
	O/P Even Though Local Variable is final, Before using only we have to perform initialization.
*/

/*
	For Local Variable Only Final keyword is applicable.
*/